    "# Leonardo's Aerial Screw: The First Helicopter Concept\n",
    "\n",
    "```{admonition} Historical Context\n",
    ":class: note\n",
    "The aerial screw, designed around 1485-1490, represents Leonardo's vision of vertical flight. Found in the Paris Manuscript B, this helical rotor design predated the modern helicopter by over 450 years.\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Explore Leonardo's helicopter concept through interactive physics simulation and discover why his design principles remain valid today."
